DefaultReaderConfiguration.fullDescription: Collects SSL VPN authentication and VPN access events on Netilla VPN applicances.

file.toolTipText: Directory or path to read from

string.toolTipText: Hostname of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

integer.toolTipText: Port number of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

select.toolTipText: Data routing (normalized alerts to Manager and/or raw data to nDepth)

integer.toolTipText: Number of seconds between log reads

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ rppd: Result=\w+ R=[-\w.]+ U=\S+ H=\S+ Pa=.+ I=[\d.]* Po=\d+ Pr=\w+ Msg=.*
^\d+ [-\w.]+ transportd\[\d+\]: [-\w]+: Connection to local server [-\w.]+ established successfully

FastFormatter.format: ControlAddr: $9, Delay: $10, Xdelay: $11, Mailer: $12, Priority: $13, DSN: $14, Status: $15

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ transportd\[\d+\]: \w+: SSL server started on port \d+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ Tarantella: Shutting down Thin Client Services
^\d+ [-\w.]+ jarmpd\[\d+\]: Got terminating signal \d+\. +Shutting down server

FastFormatter.condition: (\w+ emulator session for .+?/cn=.+) Application: (.+?/cn=.+) Desktop server: (.+) Application server: (.+?/cn=.+) Client: ([-\w.]+) Security method: (.*)
FastFormatter.format: $7, Application: $8, Desktop Server: $9, Application Server: $10, Client: $11, Security Method: $12

FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) ([^:]+): (\w+): (\d+): Attempting to connect session for user: (\S+) in realm: (\S+) with IP address ([\d.]+).*
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ psvpnd-svr-chld: \w+: \d+: Attempting to connect session for user:

FastField.defaultValue: $4: attempting to connect session for user $6

FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) ([^:]+): (\w+: SSL VPN session initiated for user: \S+) in realm: (\S+) with IP address ([\d.]+).*
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ psvpnd-svr: \w+: SSL VPN session initiated for user

FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) ([^:]+): (\w+: SSL VPN session terminated after \d+ seconds for user: \S+) in realm: (\S+).*

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ mad: Login failure: Realm='[^']+' User='[^']+' Failstage='[^']*'

FastField.defaultValue: Logon failure for user "$5" for realm $4

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ sshd\[\d+\]: Failed password for (\S+) from [-\w.]+ port \d+ \w+

FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) ([^:]+): (Failed password for illegal user (\S+) from ([-\w.]+) port( \d+)) (\w+).*
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ sshd\[\d+\]: Failed password for illegal user \S+ from [-\w.]+ port \d+ \w+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ jarmpd\[\d+\]: \[\w+\] User: \S+\\\S+; query: \(IP\)[-\w.]+:\d+, proto: TCP, origin: \w+, res: \w+

FastField.defaultValue: Received $4 query to $7 from user $6; Result: $11

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ jarmpd\[\d+\]: \[\w+\] Received query: [-\w.]+:\d+, proto: TCP, res: \w+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ jarmpd\[\d+\]: \[\w+\] User: \S+\\\S+; query: \(IP\)[-\w.]+:\d+, proto: UDP, origin: \w+, res: \w+

FastField.defaultValue: Received $4 query to $7 from user $6; Result: $11

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ jarmpd\[\d+\]: \[\w+\] Received query: [-\w.]+:\d+, proto: UDP, res: \w+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ jarmpd\[\d+\]: \[\w+\] User: \S+\\\S+; query: \(IP\)[-\w.]+:\d+, proto: \w+, origin: \w+, res: \w+

FastField.defaultValue: Received $4 query to $7 from user $6; Result: $11
